I. LEAVE REQUEST SUBMISSION TEMPLATE IMPLEMENTATION

The development of user-facing templates for the individual leave request submission interface proceeded with comprehensive implementation of HTML templates designed to present the IndividualLeaveForm to student users in an intuitive and accessible manner.

The leave submission template implementation encompasses the following components:

   • Form Rendering: The template renders the IndividualLeaveForm fields using Django template form rendering capabilities including:
     - Automatic field generation with appropriate HTML input types
     - Label association with form fields for accessibility
     - Help text and placeholder displays providing user guidance
     - CSRF token inclusion for security compliance
   
   • Date Picker Components: Interactive date selection components were integrated including:
     - JavaScript-based date picker widgets enabling intuitive date selection
     - Date format specification ensuring consistent user input
     - Calendar visualization for date range selection
     - Validation feedback for date selection constraints
   
   • Reason Text Area: A comprehensive text input component for leave reason documentation including:
     - Multi-line text area for detailed reason specification
     - Character count display showing input length
     - Placeholder text guiding users on expected content
     - Real-time validation feedback
   
   • Submission Controls: Interface elements facilitating form submission and cancellation including:
     - Submit button for form submission
     - Cancel button for user cancellation
     - Help and support links for user assistance

This comprehensive submission template provides an intuitive interface for student leave request submission.


II. LEAVE REQUEST TRACKING AND STATUS DASHBOARD

The implementation of leave request tracking and display templates proceeded with development of student-focused dashboard interfaces enabling users to view their leave request submissions and track approval status.

The tracking dashboard implementation encompasses the following components:

   • Request List Display: A tabular display listing all leave requests submitted by the authenticated student including:
     - Leave request identifiers and submission dates
     - Leave date ranges and calculated duration
     - Current workflow status indicators
     - Request action links (view details, modify pending requests, cancel if applicable)
   
   • Status Indicators: Visual status indicators providing clear workflow status communication:
     - PENDING_MENTOR: Yellow/amber status indicating awaiting Mentor review
     - MENTOR_APPROVED: Blue status indicating Mentor approval completed
     - PENDING_HOD: Orange status indicating awaiting HOD review
     - HOD_APPROVED: Green status indicating fully approved
     - REJECTED: Red status indicating request rejection
     - CANCELLED: Gray status indicating cancelled by student
   
   • Request Detail View: Comprehensive display of individual request details including:
     - Student information and request identifier
     - Leave date specifications and calculated duration
     - Provided leave reason and justification
     - Complete workflow history showing all status changes and timestamps
     - Approval authority comments and decisions
     - Contact information for relevant approval authorities

This comprehensive tracking dashboard enables students to monitor leave request progression and understand approval status.


III. MENTOR AND HOD APPROVAL INTERFACE TEMPLATES

The implementation of approval authority interfaces proceeded with development of specialized templates enabling Mentors and HODs to review and approve/reject leave requests.

The approval interface implementation encompasses the following components:

   • Approval Queue Display: A prioritized list of pending requests requiring approval action:
     - Request summary information (student, dates, duration)
     - Request submission timestamp
     - Priority indicators based on leave date proximity
     - Action links for request review and approval decisions
   
   • Request Review Interface: Comprehensive detail display for individual request review including:
     - Complete student information and identification
     - Leave date specifications with visual calendar display
     - Provided leave reason and justification
     - Historical workflow information and prior approvals
     - Related coursework or academic schedule information
   
   • Approval Decision Controls: Interface elements enabling approval/rejection decisions:
     - Approve button with optional comment field
     - Reject button with required reason field
     - Return/request additional information option
     - Bulk action capabilities for multiple request processing

This comprehensive approval interface enables efficient leave request review and authorization by appropriate approval authorities.

